create

public int create(int netID,
                  int tmID,
                  java.lang.Object[] sources,
                  java.lang.String shortestPathAlg)
Same as create(int, int, Object[]) but shortest path algorithm implementation can be selected. When using DIJKSTRA, custom property "latency" of edges and vertices is used to guide the algorithm. If an edge has no latency defined unity (1) is assumed. If a vertex has no latency defined zero (0) is assumed.

getBetweenness

public java.lang.Object[] getBetweenness(int algID,
                                         int[] vertices)
Returns an array of betweenness values of the given vertices in the given Brandes algorithm instance. The order of the betweenness values in the array corresponds to the order of the given vertices.
